# The format of this file is identical to `.dockerignore`.
# It is used to reduce the size of deployed images to make the process of publishing faster.

# No need to store the pnpm store twice.
.local

# v0.7.18 — Aggressive exclusions so the deploy snapshot stays small
# AND so deploy never reuses a stale build artifact. Before this fix,
# the deploy was uploading the workspace's entire ~2.7 GB of build
# detritus (438 MB stale .next/standalone left over from a v0.7.4.1
# era, the 2.3 GB hoisted node_modules, the Electron desktop bundles,
# release ZIPs, installer downloads). Replit re-installs deps and
# re-runs `next build` on its own, so none of these need to ship.
# Critically: shipping a stale `.next/` lets Replit fall back to the
# old standalone server when the fresh build fails, which is exactly
# what was keeping production stuck at v0.7.4.1 — every Republish
# was silently reusing the prebuilt server from the snapshot instead
# of promoting the new code.

# Dependencies (re-installed by deploy)
node_modules/
**/node_modules/

# Next.js build output (regenerated by `next build` on deploy)
.next/
**/.next/
**/.turbo/
.turbo/

# Electron desktop build outputs (only relevant to BUILD.bat on Windows)
dist-electron/
dist-electron-ui/
**/dist-electron/
**/dist-electron-ui/

# Release artifacts produced LOCALLY for distribution to operators
exports/
download/
**/exports/
**/download/

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
*.log
*.tsbuildinfo

# Screenshots / uploads from chat (not referenced by app code)
attached_assets/

# Git history (deploy doesn't need it)
.git/
